erdana,Arial" SIZE=1>1</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>2/23/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>10:55:14 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">newb warrior looking for advice</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I have been playing Eq for a few months now wanted to start and alt.  I have a 42 driud and want to mix it up a bit, so I made a halfling warrior.  I though it would be nice to not get hit so, I put 25 pts into agi and the other 5 into str.  The warrior in only lvl 17 so I haven't had much experience with him.  The main question is am I wasting my time or should I restart?  If you think its a good idea to restart, some advise on race and where to put stats.<br>
<br>
many thanks,<br>
Kokbonck<br>
Lvl 17th warrior Tarew Marr</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2F2F4F><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugaldaranbladestrike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galdaran Bladestrike</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>knows that Warriors are Superior</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>18</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>2/23/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>11:43:09 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">well</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">You'll still be able to be a good warrior, but your hp's will never match that of an ogre, large races also have the advantage of slam, which personnally i think is a HUGE advantage.<br>
