<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2F2F4F><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucorranndarklighter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corrann Darklighter</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>knows that Warriors are Superior</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>34</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>2/23/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>1:11:43 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://24.7.174.143/pics/cdhead.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: well</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">coppie, your still young, and i'd recommend a trick a learned at 35.<br>
<br>
while Dual Wielding, carry a shield.  What I did was in my first set of 10 hot keys I dropped a copy of my melee2 slot and an inventory slot. I keep a shield in the inv slot at all times. (i only DW now unfortunately)<br>
<br>
During a fight, I pick up the shield from the hot key box and hold it with my cursor.  Everytime Bash comes up I quickly drop the shield into place and pickup the offhand weap, hit bash, and immediately drop the weap back in place.  Since 35, and really only since 41 or so when I haven't been fighting mobs requiring magic weaps to hit, I have bashed this way. Only in the last 3 levels or so have I had a magical shield to bash with.<br>
<br>
My skill has gone from 50 to 150 in the course of about 8 levels, so if you were to start now, you'd have no problems keeping bash nearly maxxed.  It has become very useful as it does stop runners, stuns them sometimes during combat, breaks casts by casters, etc.  <br>
<br>
but i would think having some decent agi would help with taking less hits. as i have picked up from reading here, str doesn't seem to be as huge a factor as everyone originally thought. it's important, but won't make you useless if low. I'm a 48 warrior and only have 136 str without a Wurmslayer loaded, and I hit fine and tank like a dwarf =)  I can take hits like the best of um so I wouldn't be worried, just have fun ! <br>
<br>
</font><P><img src="http://24.7.174.143/files/cdlotmlogo.gif"><BR><br><img src="http://24.7.174.143/files/motto.gif">
<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udraky.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Draky</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>knows that Warriors are Superior</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>5</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>2/23/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>2:20:34 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: well</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">17 is not that far in! When deciding what race of warrior I wanted to play I made a few warriors and got them all up to level 18 before I decided (stupid of me not to get them all past the damage cap, level 20). Halfing, Halfelf, and DE were all gone. I stuck with one of my 2 barbs. If I was to start all over with another warrior today I would make an ogre and max out his STA to 150 and then put the remaining points into DEX or STR. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P>Draky
